    "causal_summary": "An adversarial review (GPT-5.6 SOL, ultra) of the `create-diff` engine and its redesigned HTML report, independently re-verified against the source, found real defects in three areas: (1) the engine decodes text with `errors=\"replace\"` and only sniffs a NUL byte for binary, so two files differing only in invalid bytes both become `�` and are reported identical at \"full fidelity\" — silent difference-erasure; (2) the diff line model splits on `\"\\n\"`, so empty files and trailing-newline-only differences produce phantom or mislabelled lines; (3) `validatereport.py` regex-matches tags and only",
